  "texts": [
    "This characteristic is largely a result of the unique cellular structure of the husks, which, even after burning, retain a porous form.",
    "This porosity enhances the material reactivity as a SCM.",
    "Thus, the transformation of rice husks from an agricultural residue into a valuable construction material highlights the sustainability potential of using RHA to improve concrete properties [36].",
    "GGBFSGGBFS, is a SCM produced in blast furnaces, which are also used in iron production.",
    "These furnaces operate at around 1600°C, where a combination of limestone, coke, and iron ore is converted into two main products: molten iron and molten slag."
